  "text": "The Apache Kafka plugin/extension loading system implements interface-based dependency injection through a sophisticated classloader hierarchy and reflection-based plugin scanning mechanism.\n\n## Core Plugin Interfaces\nThe plugin system defines abstract base classes and interfaces in the `connect/api` package:\n- **Connector** (sg-evals/kafka--0753c489:connect/api/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/connect/connector/Connector.java): Abstract base class for all connectors, defining the interface for managing data integration. Implementations must be either SourceConnector or SinkConnector.\n- **SourceConnector** (sg-evals/kafka--0753c489:connect/api/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/connect/source/SourceConnector.java): Extends Connector for ingesting data into Kafka.\n- **SinkConnector** (sg-evals/kafka--0753c489:connect/api/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/connect/sink/SinkConnector.java): Extends Connector for exporting data from Kafka.\n- **Converter** (sg-evals/kafka--0753c489:connect/api/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/connect/storage/Converter.java): Interface for translating between Kafka Connect's runtime data format and byte arrays. Uses ServiceLoader for discovery.\n- **HeaderConverter** (sg-evals/kafka--0753c489:connect/api/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/connect/storage/HeaderConverter.java): Similar to Converter but specifically for message headers. Discovered via Java ServiceLoader mechanism.\n- **Task** (sg-evals/kafka--0753c489:connect/api/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/connect/connector/Task.java): Base interface for task implementations that perform the actual data copying.\n- **ConnectorContext** (sg-evals/kafka--0753c489:connect/api/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/connect/connector/ConnectorContext.java): Interface allowing connectors to interact with the Kafka Connect runtime.\n- **SourceTaskContext** and **SinkTaskContext** (sg-evals/kafka--0753c489:connect/api/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/connect/source/SourceTaskContext.java, sg-evals/kafka--0753c489:connect/api/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/connect/sink/SinkTaskContext.java): Context interfaces for source and sink tasks respectively.\n\n## Plugin Type Enumeration\n**PluginType** (sg-evals/kafka--0753c489:connect/runtime/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/connect/runtime/isolation/PluginType.java) is an enum defining all plugin categories:\n- SOURCE (SourceConnector.class)\n- SINK (SinkConnector.class)\n- CONVERTER (Converter.class)\n- HEADER_CONVERTER (HeaderConverter.class)\n- TRANSFORMATION (Transformation.class)\n- PREDICATE (Predicate.class)\n- CONFIGPROVIDER (ConfigProvider.class)\n- REST_EXTENSION (ConnectRestExtension.class)\n- CONNECTOR_CLIENT_CONFIG_OVERRIDE_POLICY\n\n## Plugin Scanning and Reflection-Based Discovery\nThe system uses two complementary scanning strategies:\n\n**PluginScanner** (sg-evals/kafka--0753c489:connect/runtime/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/connect/runtime/isolation/PluginScanner.java): Abstract base class with methods:\n- `discoverPlugins(Set<PluginSource>)`: Entry point for scanning all plugin sources\n- `scanPlugins(PluginSource)`: Implementation-specific strategy (abstract)\n- `getServiceLoaderPluginDesc()`: Uses Java ServiceLoader for plugin discovery\n- `scanUrlsAndAddPlugins()`: Internal method handling each source\n\n**ReflectionScanner** (sg-evals/kafka--0753c489:connect/runtime/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/connect/runtime/isolation/ReflectionScanner.java): Implements legacy discovery using ClassGraph to scan for classes implementing plugin interfaces via reflection. The `scanPlugins()` method:\n- Uses ClassGraph to scan all classes in the classloader\n- Calls `getPluginDesc()` for each plugin type (SINK, SOURCE, CONVERTER, HEADER_CONVERTER, TRANSFORMATION, PREDICATE)\n- Instantiates plugins to extract version information\n- Validates classpath consistency\n\n**ServiceLoaderScanner** (sg-evals/kafka--0753c489:connect/runtime/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/connect/runtime/isolation/ServiceLoaderScanner.java): Implements modern discovery using Java's ServiceLoader mechanism exclusively. The `scanPlugins()` method calls `getServiceLoaderPluginDesc()` for each plugin type, loading plugins declared in `META-INF/services/` manifest files.\n\n**PluginScanResult** (sg-evals/kafka--0753c489:connect/runtime/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/connect/runtime/isolation/PluginScanResult.java): Container holding discovered plugins organized by type (SortedSet<PluginDesc<T>> for each type).\n\n## PluginDesc - Generic Plugin Descriptor\n**PluginDesc** (sg-evals/kafka--0753c489:connect/runtime/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/connect/runtime/isolation/PluginDesc.java) is a generic class holding:\n- `klass`: The Class<?> of the plugin\n- `name`: Fully qualified class name\n- `version`: Plugin version (from Versioned interface)\n- `type`: PluginType enum\n- `loader`: ClassLoader responsible for loading this plugin\n\nPlugins are compared and sorted by version, location, and type to support multi-versioning.\n\n## Classloader Hierarchy - Child-First Delegation\n\n**PluginClassLoader** (sg-evals/kafka--0753c489:connect/runtime/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/connect/runtime/isolation/PluginClassLoader.java): Custom URLClassLoader implementing child-first classloading:\n- Loads plugin classes from its own URLs first\n- Delegates to parent for classes not found or those that shouldn't be isolated\n- Thread-safe and parallel-capable (marked with `ClassLoader.registerAsParallelCapable()`)\n- Stores the `pluginLocation` (top-level plugin path) for tracking plugin sources\n\n**DelegatingClassLoader** (sg-evals/kafka--0753c489:connect/runtime/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/connect/runtime/isolation/DelegatingClassLoader.java): Master classloader orchestrating isolation:\n- Acts as child-first classloader, delegating plugin loading to child PluginClassLoaders\n- Maintains `pluginLoaders`: ConcurrentMap<String, SortedMap<PluginDesc<?>, ClassLoader>> for managing multiple versions\n- Maintains `aliases`: ConcurrentMap for plugin name aliases\n- Methods:\n  - `pluginClassLoader(name, range, connectorLoader)`: Retrieves the appropriate PluginClassLoader for a plugin by version\n  - `loadClass(name, resolve)`: Implements child-first loading - searches plugin loaders first, then delegates to parent\n  - `installDiscoveredPlugins(scanResult)`: Registers discovered plugins with their classloaders\n  - `connectorLoader(connectorName)`: Retrieves the classloader for a specific connector\n\n**ClassLoaderFactory** (sg-evals/kafka--0753c489:connect/runtime/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/connect/runtime/isolation/ClassLoaderFactory.java): Factory for creating DelegatingClassLoader and PluginClassLoader instances, with security manager support.\n\n## Plugin Source and Isolation Decision\n\n**PluginSource** (sg-evals/kafka--0753c489:connect/runtime/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/connect/runtime/isolation/PluginSource.java): Record class representing a plugin source with:\n- `location`: Path to the plugin directory\n- `type`: CLASSPATH or ISOLATED\n- `loader`: ClassLoader for this source\n- `urls`: Array of URLs to scan\n\n**PluginUtils** (sg-evals/kafka--0753c489:connect/runtime/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/connect/runtime/isolation/PluginUtils.java): Utility methods for plugin management:\n- `shouldLoadInIsolation(className)`: Determines if a class should be loaded in isolation using EXCLUDE/INCLUDE regex patterns\n- `pluginSources(pluginLocations, delegatingClassLoader, factory)`: Creates PluginSource objects from configured plugin paths\n- `isolatedPluginSource()` and `classpathPluginSource()`: Factory methods for specific source types\n- `simpleName()`, `prunedName()`: Plugin naming utilities for aliases\n\n## Main Plugin Orchestrator - Plugins Class\n\n**Plugins** (sg-evals/kafka--0753c489:connect/runtime/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/connect/runtime/isolation/Plugins.java) is the central plugin management class:\n\n**Plugin Discovery and Installation:**\n- `initLoaders(pluginSources, discoveryMode)`: Initializes the plugin loading system\n  - Creates DelegatingClassLoader and PluginClassLoader instances\n  - Runs PluginScanner (ReflectionScanner or ServiceLoaderScanner) to discover plugins\n  - Returns merged PluginScanResult\n\n**Plugin Instantiation with Dependency Injection:**\n- `newPlugin(classOrAlias, range)`: Creates plugin instances with version support\n  - Resolves plugin aliases\n  - Uses pluginLoader() to get the appropriate ClassLoader\n  - Instantiates the plugin class with proper classloader context\n  - Configurable via LoaderSwap for context switching\n\n- `newPlugin(classOrAlias, range, sourceLoader)`: Creates plugins from a specific source classloader\n\n- `newConnector()`: Factory for creating Connector instances\n- `newConverter()`: Factory for creating Converter instances with `configure(config, isKey)` dependency injection\n- `newHeaderConverter()`: Factory for creating HeaderConverter instances\n- `newPlugins()`: Batch creation of multiple plugin instances\n\n**Plugin Querying:**\n- `sourceConnectors(alias)`, `sinkConnectors(alias)`: Retrieve connector plugin descriptors\n- `converters(alias)`, `headerConverters(alias)`: Retrieve converter plugin descriptors\n- `pluginVersion()`: Get version of a specific plugin\n- `pluginClass()`: Get the Class<?> of a plugin\n\n**Classloader Management:**\n- `delegatingLoader()`: Returns the master DelegatingClassLoader\n- `connectorLoader(connectorName)`: Gets the classloader for a connector\n- `pluginLoader(classOrAlias, range, sourceLoader)`: Internal method resolving the appropriate classloader\n- `withClassLoader(loader)`: Returns LoaderSwap for temporarily changing context classloader\n- `safeLoaderSwapper()`: Returns a safe variant of LoaderSwap\n\n## LoaderSwap - Context Switching\n\n**LoaderSwap** (sg-evals/kafka--0753c489:connect/runtime/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/connect/runtime/isolation/LoaderSwap.java): Implements AutoCloseable for automatic classloader restoration:\n```java\ntry (LoaderSwap loaderSwap = plugins.withClassLoader(pluginClassLoader)) {\n    plugin.configure(config);\n    // Operations here execute with pluginClassLoader as context\n}\n// Original classloader automatically restored\n```\n\n## Configuration and Dependency Resolution\n\n**ConnectorConfig** (sg-evals/kafka--0753c489:connect/runtime/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/connect/runtime/ConnectorConfig.java): Base configuration class for connectors\n- Defines standard connector configuration keys\n- Includes key.converter and value.converter dependency injection\n- Validates configuration and creates typed plugin instances\n\n**SourceConnectorConfig** and **SinkConnectorConfig**: Connector-specific configuration subclasses\n\n## REST API and Plugin Metadata\n\n**ConnectorPluginsResource** (sg-evals/kafka--0753c489:connect/runtime/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/connect/runtime/rest/resources/ConnectorPluginsResource.java): REST endpoint providing:\n- GET /connector-plugins: Lists all installed connector plugins\n- GET /connector-plugins/{plugin-type}/config: Configuration schema for a plugin\n\n**PluginInfo** (sg-evals/kafka--0753c489:connect/runtime/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/connect/runtime/rest/entities/PluginInfo.java): DTO containing plugin metadata (className, type, version)\n\n## Key Design Patterns\n\n1. **Interface-Based Plugin Architecture**: All plugins implement standard interfaces (Connector, Converter, HeaderConverter, etc.)\n\n2. **Multi-Level Classloading with Child-First Delegation**: \n   - PluginClassLoader loads plugin-specific classes\n   - DelegatingClassLoader orchestrates multiple isolated plugin loaders\n   - Prevents version conflicts between plugins\n\n3. **Reflection-Based Discovery**: Uses classgraph library to scan classpath for implementations\n\n4. **ServiceLoader Integration**: Modern Java SPI mechanism for declarative plugin discovery via META-INF/services\n\n5. **Dependency Injection via Context Switching**: LoaderSwap and withClassLoader enable the runtime to ensure plugins execute with the correct classloader context, allowing dependency injection through standard Java interfaces like Configurable\n\n6. **Version Management**: PluginDesc supports multi-versioning, allowing different versions of the same plugin to coexist\n\n7. **Lazy Instantiation**: Plugins are discovered at scan time but instantiated only when needed\n\nThis architecture enables Kafka Connect to load and manage plugins with complete isolation, preventing classpath conflicts while maintaining clean interface-based contracts for dependency injection."
